<section xml:id="EHTL_Epigraph">
  <title>Epigraph</title>
  <p>
    Energy is eternal delight
  </p>
  <p>
    William Blake (1757<mdash/>1827),
    <em>The Marriage of Heaven and Hell</em>, The Poetical Works, 1908.
    Besides energy,
    no other general concept finds application is all domains of science....In the last analysis,everything that happens is nothing but changes in energy.
  </p>
  <p>
    Wilhelm Ostwald (1853<mdash/>1932), Translated by Robert Bruce Lindsay, 1976, Applications of Energy: Nineteenth Century (Benchmark Papers on Energy, V2), John Wiley &amp; Sons
  </p>
</section>